Biography

2022-2023: Appeared in 15 games for the PLU women's basketball team. Finished the season averaging .302 from the field and a total of 8 points.

2021-2022: Appeared in 21 games for the Lutes making 6 starts on the season. Finished the season averaging 3.6 points per game and 4.2 rebounds per game. Had 22 steals on the season and had a season best 9 points and 10 rebounds against Whitworth on February 11th.

2021: Appeared in one game for the Lutes this season.

High School: Earned four varsity letters at Franklin Pierce HS and was named a team captain for two seasons and team MVP twice. She was a South Puget Sound League 2A First Team for three seasons. After he junior year, Cook was nominated for the Tacoma Athletic Commission Athlete of the Year Award. Also earned four letters in softball and volleyball at Franklin Pierce.

Personal: Is the daughter of Tom and Janet and sister to Audrey and Emily. She plans on teaching physical education after PLU and her hobbies include jet skiing, hiking and baking.

Major: Kinesiology-Educations

Favorite Team: Gonzaga Men's Basketball

Favorite Athlete: Sabrina Ionescu

Favorite Music: Hip-hop and country
